e
	are no problems when we&#39;re writing the job-data to the local
disk of
	th=
at server. But when a symbolic link is made from
&#39;$HERITRIX_HOME/jobs&#39;
	to =
an NFS-mount, the java-proces (the JVM I presume) gets
&#39;defunct&#39;, and
	cann=
ot be killed, not even with &#39;kill -9 PID&#39; or a &#39;killall -9
PID&#39;.










=
I&#39;ve not seen that before but then we don&#39;t run on NFS mounts.  Anything
in=
 the server system logs that you can correlate with the process going
defun=
ct?  Is the system complaining about NFS volume being unreachable.





