s happens when a new job is being created through Heritrix&#39; web-ui.
After t=
his, Heritrix does not respond anymore and the server has to be
rebooted. T=
his is how the proces looks like:

$ ps aux
USER PID %CPU %MEM VSZ RSS TTY =
STAT START TIME COMMAND
...
bart 7911 2.0 0.0 0 0 ? Zl 09:50 0:03 [java]
&lt;d=
efunct&gt;
...

We&#39;re using:

* Heritrix 1.10.1
* Sun&#39;s JRE 1.5.0 update 10
* =
Linux Red Hat AS 4

On the following page I found something about problems =
while writing to
an NFS mount:
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/releasen=
otes.html#1_10_0_limitations
&lt;http://crawler.archive.org/articles/releaseno=
tes.html#1_10_0_limitation
s&gt; 

-------------------------------------------=
---------------
1.2.1. java.io.IOException: No locks available
BDB-JE will =
complain &#39;No locks available&#39; when crawler is 
being built/run on an NFS mo=
unt. Workaround is to locate 
the &#39;state&#39; directory on a non-NFS-mounted vo=
lume.
----------------------------------------------------------

