ns showed in the UI in the list of alerts (and then
probably in heritrix_ou=
t.log).  

Have you tried locating the Heritrix state on local disk?  Or is=
 local
disk too small?

Around here, a process is run to offload ARCs as cr=
awl progresses.
Would such a process work for you offloading ARCs and logs =
to the NFS
mount?

St.Ack






Neither is it thrown and
displayed in Herit=
rix&#39; web-ui. Also, it doesn&#39;t mention anything about a
defunct proces, so I=
&#39;m not sure if this is the problem at hand. And it
says &quot;being built/run on=
 an NFS mount&quot;, where in our case, Heritrix
merely writes the job-data to t=
he NFS-mount.









Has any of you encountered this before?











K=
ind regards,

Bart Kiers.






